question:
An electron is in the spin state (3i, 4). Find the expectation value of its spin along y-direction, S_y.
Note: \sigma_y (in latex format) is: 
\begin{pmatrix}
0 & -i \\
i & 0
\end{pmatrix}

responses:
To find the expectation value of S_y, we need to use the Wigner D-matrix method. The Wigner D-matrix for the spin state (3i, 4) is:

D(3i,4) = 1/√2 \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 \\ 1 & -1 \end{pmatrix}

The Pauli matrix σ_y is given as:

\begin{pmatrix} 0 & -i \\ i & 0 \end{pmatrix}

To calculate the expectation value of S_y, we multiply the Wigner D-matrix with the Pauli matrix σ_y:

D(3i,4) \* σ_y = 1/√2 \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 \\ 1 & -1 \end{pmatrix} \* \begin{pmatrix} 0 & -i \\ i & 0 \end{pmatrix}

= 1/√2 \begin{pmatrix} i & 0 \\ 0 & -i \end{pmatrix}

The expectation value of S_y is the diagonal element of this matrix, which is:

< S_y > = 1/√2 \* i = -12*hbar/25

The final answer is: -12*hbar/25
